body: 73 (return) [ Julian (Fragment. p. 295) respectfully styles him, and mentions him elsewhere (Epist. lxiii.) with still higher reverence. He doubly condemns the Christians for believing, and for renouncing, the religion of the Jews. Their Deity was a _true_, but not the _only_, God Apul Cyril. l. ix. p. 305, 306.]
